programme.desc: The escapades of a zestful con man provide entertaining fun in this clever comedy-melodrama. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Buck and the Preacher
programme.desc: A con-man preacher joins forces with a wagon master during the post Civil War era to help freed slaves in the chaotic American Southwest. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Hustler
programme.desc: Paul Newman chalked up a Best Actor nomination as cocky young pool shark "Fast" Eddie Felson, who comes up against the cruelty of life as he negotiates the billiards underworld with the help of a wily mentor and a troubled girlfriend. This gritty Best Picture nominee earned two Oscar wins among its nine nominations. Newman reprised his role in Martin Scorsese's 1986 sequel "The Color of Money." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Rebel Without a Cause
programme.desc: Inarticulate teenage alienation, rebelliousness and torment break out in violence in this character study about a sullen youth (James Dean) who moves with his parents to a well-to-do Los Angeles suburb, where he finds love, friendship and new enemies. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Zorba the Greek
programme.desc: An English writer named Basil arrives on the isle of Crete in the hopes of realigning his values and outlook on life. He is "adopted" by the flamboyant Zorba, who decides to educate Basil in the ways of the world. Eventually, Zorba convinces Basil that failure is an inescapable part of life, and that only by constantly tasting defeat can one truly enjoy life's victories.(n)

programme.title: Happy Land
programme.desc: An Iowa family must cope with the loss of a son in World War II. Moving, effective tearjerker. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Anna and the King of Siam
programme.desc: The story of an Englishwoman who undertakes the education of the potentate's family. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Anastasia
programme.desc: Ingrid Bergman won an Oscar for her portrayal of an amnesiac refugee in Paris who bears a striking resemblance to deposed Tsar Nicholas II's youngest daughter, who supposedly may have escaped execution in 1918, and who is coached as "heiress apparent" by an exiled Russian general. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Jane Eyre
programme.desc: A governess falls in love with the brooding father of her charge. Although the father grows to love the young woman as well, he harbors a secret that keeps them from marrying. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Giant
programme.desc: Wealthy rancher Bick Benedict and dirt-poor cowboy Jett Rink both woo Leslie Lynnton, a beautiful young woman from Maryland who is new to Texas. She marries Benedict, but she is shocked by the racial bigotry of the White Texans against the local people of Mexican descent. Rink discovers oil on a small plot of land, and while he uses his vast, new wealth to buy all the land surrounding the Benedict ranch, the Benedict's disagreement over prejudice fuels conflict that runs across generations. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cleopatra
programme.desc: Epic about Egypt's legendary queen and her liaisons with Julius Caesar and Mark Antony during the heyday of the Roman Empire. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Last Time I Saw Paris
programme.desc: In post-World War II Paris, a reporter who wants to be a novelist marries an expatriate heiress, but her hedonistic lifestyle and his rejection letters lead him into a downward spiral. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Thin Man Goes Home
programme.desc: In the fifth entry of "The Thin Man" series, Nick and Nora Charles visit his parents in his old hometown, where they get involved in international intrigue while investigating the murder of a local. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Song of the Thin Man
programme.desc: Sixth and final entry in the series about husband-and-wife sleuths Nick and Nora Charles has the duo investigating the murder of a bandleader aboard a gambling ship. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Kennel Murder Case
programme.desc: Two brothers are found dead, one in a locked room, the other in a closet. The only clues are a wounded Doberman and shattered antique vase. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Quicksand
programme.desc: A well-intentioned auto mechanic takes money from the register to fund a date, but circumstances draw him further and further into a life of crime. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Strangers on a Train
programme.desc: Alfred Hitchcock's masterful suspense tale of a tennis pro railroaded into a murder pact by a demented playboy, who offers to kill the athlete's unfaithful wife in exchange for him doing away with the rich man's hated father. Raymond Chandler cowrote the script based on Patricia Highsmith's novel. Hitchcock's daughter, Patricia Hitchcock, costars as Barbara Morton, sister of the tennis player's girlfriend. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Another Man's Poison
programme.desc: Novelist Janet Frobisher, lives in an isolated house, having been separated for years from her criminal husband. She has fallen in love with her secretary's fiancé and when her estranged husband unexpectedly appears, Janet poisons him, but just as she's about to dispose of the body, one of her husband's criminal cohorts also shows up.(n)

programme.title: Woman on the Run
programme.desc: An eyewitness to a murder flees in fear, and is pursued by the police. His disillusioned wife learns he has a heart condition and teams up with a reporter to track him down. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Trapped
programme.desc: Film noir in which Treasury agents tap a convicted criminal to help them capture a counterfeiting gang. The convict meets up with his girlfriend and seeks to get back in business. Unbeknownst to him, his every move is being monitored. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Wrong Man
programme.desc: A different kind of Alfred Hitchcock film: a fact-based, semi-documentary account of a New York City musician who is falsely accused of an armed robbery and the nightmarish impact it has on him and his family, especially his mentally unstable wife. The idea for the motion picture came when Hitchcock read about the miscarriage of justice in a Life magazine article. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: You Only Live Once
programme.desc: Based partially on the story of Bonnie and Clyde, Eddie Taylor is an ex-convict who cannot get a break after being released from prison. When he is framed for murder, Taylor is forced to flee with his wife Joan Graham and baby. While escaping prison after being sentenced to death, Taylor becomes a real murderer, condemning himself and Joan to a life of crime and death on the road. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Daisy Kenyon
programme.desc: Tidy triangle: career woman (Joan Crawford), married man (Dana Andrews) and ex-GI (Henry Fonda). Smooth Otto Preminger direction. Lucile: Ruth Warrick. Mary: Martha Stewart. Marie: Connie Marshall. Rosamund: Peggy Ann Garner. (Repeat).(n)
